cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its accompanying paper, please cite it as below."
title: "SynthFix: Adaptive Neural-Symbolic Code Vulnerability Repair"
abstract: >
  SynthFix is a hybrid training framework for LLM-based code
  vulnerability repair. It combines Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT)
  with Reward Fine-Tuning (RFT) through a lightweight neural router
  that adaptively gates the symbolic reward signal based on
  per-sample difficulty features. The symbolic reward is split into
  AST, CFG, semantic, and surface-similarity components, yielding a
  richer training signal than a single scalar reward.
authors:
